                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3z02zr6s/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"indent(1)\">Expedition is necessary in the printing of these\n                                        laws<lb/> no doubt you will be able to forward them by the\n                                        packet<lb/> which will sail from <placeName>New\n                                                  York</placeName> in <date>August</date>. If you\n                                        do, I shall<lb/> contrive to get you voted a piece of a\n                                        plate, until we can give<lb/> you something better.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I wrote you 2 months back by the Gt. Western.<lb/>\n                                        Did you receive my letter? Everything here looks gloomy<lb/>\n                                        owing to recent events in <placeName>Europe</placeName> and\n                                        the civil war in <placeName>Venezuela</placeName>;<lb/>\n                                        money has vanished, for the last 6 months I have recd.\n                                        no<lb/> salary and even the latter has been reduced to $1000\n                                        p annum.<lb/> I am obliged to have recourse to school shop\n                                        again, but the<lb/> establishment has every appearance and\n                                        prospect of success.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">My health is good, better than it has been<lb/>\n                                        for years past, but <persName>Mrs. Nathan</persName>, her\n                                        mother, and her aged Grand-<lb/>parent are all unwell.\n                                        Your's, I hope, is not suffering from<lb/> the summer\n                                        heats.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Present <del>my</del> our best compliments and\n                                        warmest<lb/> wishes to all our old friends. I long to see\n                                        you and have a<lb/> few good chats with you and all those of\n                                        whose kindness<lb/> we <del>I</del> entertain so lively and\n                                        grateful a recollection. Congratulate<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Miss Cousens</persName> for us, as we understand\n                                        she has been or is<lb/> about to be married. In haste</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(6)\">Most truly yours</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(6)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">M N Nathan</persName>\n                              </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3z02zr6s/canvas/p2"
